data.title: HOW SYDNEY'S HARBOUR TUNNEL WILL BE BUILT
data.meta_description: AFTER 12 months of research and planning, preliminary work has begun on the largest civil engineering project in Sydney since the Harbour Bridge - the Sydney Harbour Tunnel.
data.text:
AFTER 12 months of research and planning, preliminary work has begun on the largest civil engineering project in Sydney since the Harbour Bridge - the Sydney Harbour Tunnel.

Sponsored by a joint venture company formed by Transfield Pty Ltd, one of Australia's leading construction companies and Kumagai Gumi of Japan, the project has brought together the skills of a number of Australia's foremost engineering firms.
